1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,720
So, what do we have here?

3
00:00:03,720 --> 00:00:05,850
Glasses, we have pastries.

4
00:00:06,250 --> 00:00:08,000
We've got it all here, we've got...

5
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:08,620
What are we missing?

6
00:00:09,540 --> 00:00:11,400
Why the long face, Ivuška?

7
00:00:11,540 --> 00:00:13,520
Breakfast time, time of the gods.

8
00:00:13,920 --> 00:00:15,500
I can't watch this.

9
00:00:15,720 --> 00:00:18,540
I'm amazed you're still alive with eating habits like these.

10
00:00:18,540 --> 00:00:19,420
What do you mean still alive?

11
00:00:19,420 --> 00:00:20,680
Look how well we're doing.

12
00:00:21,220 --> 00:00:21,960
Exactly.

13
00:00:22,140 --> 00:00:23,020
And what's wrong with it?

14
00:00:23,020 --> 00:00:24,340
It's a pretty varied diet.

15
00:00:24,460 --> 00:00:25,500
Look how colorful it is.

16
00:00:26,550 --> 00:00:27,250
Besides, I'm not gonna eat any chicken feed.

17
00:00:30,020 --> 00:00:33,400
Have you ever seen a chicken that made it further than onto my plate?

18
00:00:35,320 --> 00:00:36,200
Go ahead and laugh.

19
00:00:36,420 --> 00:00:40,780
But when you each weigh two hundred kilos, I'll happily donate you to the army for bridge stress tests.

20
00:00:41,220 --> 00:00:42,240
Look at these jeans.

21
00:00:42,340 --> 00:00:44,000
I bought them at Tuzex and how they fit.

22
00:00:44,040 --> 00:00:44,860
Like a glove.

23
00:00:45,160 --> 00:00:46,960
A great fat burner, this guy.

24
00:00:47,750 --> 00:00:48,750
And a looker too.

25
00:00:51,850 --> 00:00:52,990
You've got sausages again, huh?

26
00:00:53,150 --> 00:00:53,850
What sausages?

27
00:00:57,550 --> 00:00:59,550
Sausages are for amateurs, Ivuška.

28
00:00:59,770 --> 00:01:01,950
This is a Giant in the oven.

29
00:01:05,050 --> 00:01:06,520
Simona got it, brand new, test batch.

30
00:01:06,520 --> 00:01:07,600
Did it pass the boil test?

31
00:01:08,750 --> 00:01:10,870
Exactly 240 seconds, boss.

32
00:01:10,870 --> 00:01:11,710
Excellent.

33
00:01:12,750 --> 00:01:13,580
Wait up, man.

34
00:01:14,350 --> 00:01:16,720
With the Giant comes responsibility.

35
00:01:18,550 --> 00:01:22,340
We got a pile of questionnaires and instructions here, this isn't just any sausage.

36
00:01:22,650 --> 00:01:24,550
So listen, they write.

37
00:01:24,950 --> 00:01:28,000
The Giant is not just any sausage.

38
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:28,780
I see.

39
00:01:30,050 --> 00:01:33,050
The Giant is a revolution in the meat industry.

40
00:01:33,150 --> 00:01:41,050
It also contains all the important ingredients, perfectly balanced, and on top of those, even meat.

41
00:01:41,250 --> 00:01:44,250
Well, a sausage made of meat, that's a revolution.

42
00:01:44,450 --> 00:01:49,700
After the Giant, the world will never be the same again.

43
00:01:49,950 --> 00:01:54,350
And do you realize that a whole Somali village could eat off one of these sausages?

44
00:01:54,650 --> 00:01:55,750
They couldn't, because they weren't entrusted with the Giant.

45
00:02:01,310 --> 00:02:02,710
So, bro, let's get started.

46
00:02:02,910 --> 00:02:03,610
First point.

47
00:02:04,670 --> 00:02:05,190
Juiciness.

48
00:02:09,450 --> 00:02:15,950
Ten out of ten from me.

49
00:02:19,320 --> 00:02:20,320
What's next?

50
00:02:22,850 --> 00:02:50,050
You should have seen it.

51
00:02:50,750 --> 00:02:54,050
Like two Neanderthals, I was totally grossed out.

52
00:02:54,250 --> 00:02:55,390
Have a cookie.

53
00:02:56,350 --> 00:02:59,650
Look, no added sugar, just dried fruit and cereal.

54
00:02:59,650 --> 00:03:00,970
It's so unfair.

55
00:03:01,950 --> 00:03:03,750
We'll be eating health food our whole lives so nobody calls us fat, and them.

56
00:03:06,330 --> 00:03:07,750
Your dad isn't fat though.

57
00:03:07,970 --> 00:03:09,030
Well, he should be.

58
00:03:10,250 --> 00:03:11,650
I need to calm my nerves.

59
00:03:13,950 --> 00:03:18,840
Iva, next week we're going to work out at the pool and Beneš will be there.

60
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:21,050
That's just four spoonfuls and done.

61
00:03:23,250 --> 00:03:24,910
Look at his famous jeans, okay?

62
00:03:25,150 --> 00:03:29,850
Dude, at forty they won't go on, at sixty they'll shrink on me.

63
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:31,450
And tell me, what am I supposed to do about it.

64
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:34,200
Twenty.

65
00:03:35,250 --> 00:03:36,550
Twenty's not enough in practice.

66
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:39,150
Twenty spoonfuls, Iva, you should really stop now.

67
00:03:40,550 --> 00:03:44,950
I'm so pissed off I could do ninety.

68
00:03:56,350 --> 00:03:57,650
Impossible, come on.

69
00:03:58,250 --> 00:03:59,940
Couldn't they have shrunk somehow?

70
00:03:59,940 --> 00:04:01,520
To forty, like always.

71
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:02,020
And?

72
00:04:02,220 --> 00:04:02,640
Well.

73
00:04:03,650 --> 00:04:05,150
And now try some other ones.

74
00:04:07,150 --> 00:04:09,550
Come on, get them down!

75
00:04:09,550 --> 00:04:16,670
This can't be right, I mean I've never gained weight.

76
00:04:16,850 --> 00:04:20,390
Well yeah, after the Giant nothing will ever be the same.

77
00:04:20,950 --> 00:04:21,550
It's in.

78
00:04:21,670 --> 00:04:22,330
It's in.

79
00:04:22,510 --> 00:04:22,750
Super.

80
00:04:23,570 --> 00:04:24,610
Well, I'm off.

81
00:04:24,990 --> 00:04:26,070
I'll swing by later.

82
00:04:26,250 --> 00:04:26,850
Bye.

83
00:04:27,430 --> 00:04:28,030
Hi.

84
00:04:30,850 --> 00:04:34,950
Well, bro, welcome to manhood.

85
00:04:48,450 --> 00:04:49,850
Tomáš, did something happen to you?

86
00:04:51,240 --> 00:04:52,220
I think I need some help.

87
00:04:53,190 --> 00:04:54,090
Help with what?

88
00:04:54,850 --> 00:04:57,250
For starters, with sitting down.

89
00:04:57,450 --> 00:04:58,830
I'll say just two words.

90
00:04:59,450 --> 00:05:01,450
Well, as long as it's not "forward march."

91
00:05:02,110 --> 00:05:03,170
Oak bark.

92
00:05:03,170 --> 00:05:06,050
In a few days you'll be fine again.

93
00:05:06,420 --> 00:05:07,140
Oak bark?

94
00:05:07,220 --> 00:05:07,900
Am I supposed to eat it?

95
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:09,620
Not eat it, you bathe in it.

96
00:05:10,350 --> 00:05:12,240
Marcelka, how am I supposed to bathe in bark?

97
00:05:12,240 --> 00:05:12,860
Now it's dry.

98
00:05:14,050 --> 00:05:14,850
Tomáš.

99
00:05:15,150 --> 00:05:18,780
Hemorrhoids are nothing to be ashamed of.

100
00:05:19,050 --> 00:05:21,950
Bro, I picked out some music for you.

101
00:05:23,250 --> 00:05:26,150
Michal Tučný, Věra Bílá, The Velerib Choir.

102
00:05:29,550 --> 00:05:31,750
Ozzák, Mr. Pacovský isn't fat.

103
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:33,810
Just leave it, Marcelka's right.

104
00:05:33,810 --> 00:05:36,750
Look, I've gained weight, I can't get into any pants.

105
00:05:36,810 --> 00:05:38,470
Jesus, you should have said so right away.

106
00:05:38,890 --> 00:05:40,570
Weight loss is my passion.

107
00:05:40,750 --> 00:05:43,570
If I hadn't dieted my whole life, you know what I'd look like?

108
00:05:43,810 --> 00:05:44,410
Good.

109
00:05:46,050 --> 00:05:49,050
Ozzák, we won't be needing you for this.

110
00:05:49,250 --> 00:05:51,080
Don't you want to go run some errands?

111
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:52,320
You know, I could go for one.

112
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:54,850
Well, of course, right, it's already 9:55.

113
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,520
And I'll have one for you too, bro.

114
00:05:57,620 --> 00:05:58,860
Because I can.

115
00:06:03,750 --> 00:06:05,650
And above all, no exercise.

116
00:06:06,350 --> 00:06:07,970
Are we in the Middle Ages?

117
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:14,770
Hasn't science and technology advanced enough for a person to lose weight without stinking of sweat?

118
00:06:15,150 --> 00:06:17,110
Here's a business card for a great doctor.

119
00:06:17,150 --> 00:06:19,750
A few hours of anesthesia and you're ten kilos lighter.

120
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:21,950
And couldn't we do it without the amputation?

121
00:06:23,110 --> 00:06:24,530
Liposuction, haven't you heard of it?

122
00:06:25,130 --> 00:06:26,470
Jesus, that sounds terrifying.

123
00:06:27,150 --> 00:06:29,190
Couldn't I just go on some diet instead?

124
00:06:29,450 --> 00:06:33,150
You know what, take over for me here, I'll be right back.

125
00:06:39,850 --> 00:06:41,750
Ozzák bet at the pub he could eat three kilos of ground meat, don't wait for him.

126
00:06:46,550 --> 00:06:47,690
You don't know Ozzák, when he was twelve he ate a bucket of sawdust.

127
00:06:47,690 --> 00:06:48,130
Good lord.

128
00:06:48,420 --> 00:06:49,360
And did anything happen to him?

129
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:52,150
No, he washed it down with a twelve-pack and went for seconds.

130
00:06:56,050 --> 00:06:58,450
What do you have for me?

131
00:06:59,040 --> 00:06:59,500
Science.

132
00:07:00,350 --> 00:07:01,850
So, these are special Swiss diet pills.

133
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:06,200
They're fantastic, even Madonna takes them.

134
00:07:06,460 --> 00:07:09,000
And I'll be popping pills as the pounds fall off?

135
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:09,600
Exactly.

136
00:07:09,880 --> 00:07:10,820
And your hair with them.

137
00:07:10,860 --> 00:07:12,760
But for that there are these other ones.

138
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:15,740
These actually make your hair grow, except they cause hallucinations.

139
00:07:15,860 --> 00:07:18,720
But that's solved by these fizzy ones.

140
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:24,400
The pharmacist said people sometimes throw up from them, so I also grabbed these for nausea.

141
00:07:24,740 --> 00:07:28,260
My friend took those and her face turned horribly red.

142
00:07:28,660 --> 00:07:30,480
Hence the face mask.

143
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:32,050
That one is excellent.

144
00:07:32,650 --> 00:07:34,600
And nothing will happen to me from that?

145
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:40,480
Well, they mention some allergic reaction, but these red ones take care of that for sure.

146
00:07:40,580 --> 00:07:45,360
But Tomáš, be careful with those, only one a day, otherwise you'll get terrible dizziness.

147
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:49,400
I don't take these ones because you gain a tiny bit of weight from them.

148
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:54,150
Well, but that's what the first ones are for, right?

149
00:07:55,150 --> 00:07:55,820
Exactly.

150
00:07:56,250 --> 00:08:02,450
What have you done to my father?

151
00:08:03,250 --> 00:08:07,750
I restored his self-confidence, saved his business and organized his life.

152
00:08:08,950 --> 00:08:10,950
Or are you asking about something specific?

153
00:08:18,350 --> 00:08:21,200
Tomáš, I think you've mixed things up a bit.

154
00:08:21,200 --> 00:08:23,340
I think I'm having dizzy spells.

155
00:08:23,860 --> 00:08:25,940
He shouldn't be dieting and popping pills.

156
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:29,800
No, it was those red little devils.

157
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:31,760
They were saying, take me, and I said no.

158
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:36,150
I hid from them in a little cave.

159
00:08:39,050 --> 00:08:39,550
He'll sleep it off.

160
00:08:40,980 --> 00:08:42,340
Weight loss requires sacrifices.

161
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:44,340
But we two know that well.

162
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:48,750
There's no choice but to come up with something even a man can handle.

163
00:08:56,350 --> 00:09:00,550
Ozzák, let's stretch that leg.

164
00:09:01,850 --> 00:09:03,850
What are you goofing around with?

165
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:04,500
Losing weight.

166
00:09:05,180 --> 00:09:07,140
So what about it, bro, have you decided?

167
00:09:07,340 --> 00:09:07,780
Yeah.

168
00:09:13,350 --> 00:09:15,220
Yeah, so that's how it works.

169
00:09:15,550 --> 00:09:17,150
That's just rubbing.

170
00:09:18,550 --> 00:09:19,650
As long as you're having fun.

171
00:09:20,450 --> 00:09:23,050
You know, Ivuška, science has progressed, look.

172
00:09:23,210 --> 00:09:24,570
Today you don't have to go hungry.

173
00:09:24,710 --> 00:09:26,290
I should have had this on my army march.

174
00:09:26,750 --> 00:09:27,510
This machine.

175
00:09:27,850 --> 00:09:29,850
This is a sign of progress.

176
00:09:30,210 --> 00:09:33,650
That's a sign of dementia.

177
00:09:34,470 --> 00:09:37,410
Hi, I think Ozzák is noticeably slimmer.

178
00:09:39,450 --> 00:09:41,650
I'm only doing it out of solidarity.

179
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:45,450
My figure is perfect.

180
00:09:46,350 --> 00:09:48,450
I happen to have been thinking.

181
00:09:49,450 --> 00:09:50,250
And for the sake of my bro's health, I decided to test the Giants myself.

182
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:55,680
You pig, can't you wait until it works for me?

183
00:09:56,850 --> 00:09:57,890
This is completely useless.

184
00:09:58,250 --> 00:10:00,650
It's like trying to lose weight with this marker.

185
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:02,550
Rubbing?

186
00:10:03,450 --> 00:10:04,450
Where does it go?

187
00:10:09,950 --> 00:10:11,350
This is lunch.

188
00:10:13,150 --> 00:10:14,150
Where's dinner?

189
00:10:15,850 --> 00:10:17,050
From now on, this is dinner.

190
00:10:19,050 --> 00:10:20,570
I feel kind of weak.

191
00:10:22,750 --> 00:10:26,650
Well, and when I look at Ozzák's love handles, I get my strength back.

192
00:10:26,650 --> 00:10:28,210
Those aren't love handles, bro.

193
00:10:29,450 --> 00:10:31,750
That's a maxi giant veal sausage.

194
00:10:32,650 --> 00:10:35,550
They wouldn't let me on the tram with it until I bought it a ticket.

195
00:10:35,850 --> 00:10:37,620
You're not even gonna heat it up?

196
00:10:37,650 --> 00:10:39,280
Baby, you know how warm it already is?

197
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:41,250
Rambo and I had a nice brawl.

198
00:10:41,450 --> 00:10:43,650
Uncle, how could you?

199
00:10:44,050 --> 00:10:46,250
Right when dad is starting to live healthy.

200
00:10:47,050 --> 00:10:49,650
What would an alcoholic do if you put a bottle of vodka in front of him?

201
00:10:50,450 --> 00:10:51,250
Say thanks.

202
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:54,540
Well bro, thanks a lot then.

203
00:10:54,980 --> 00:10:57,060
Get up and get out with that sausage, right now.

204
00:10:57,260 --> 00:10:59,120
Wait, wait, wait, I have rights too.

205
00:10:59,550 --> 00:11:01,620
Look, this apartment is mine, I make the decisions here.

206
00:11:01,950 --> 00:11:03,750
My house, my castle.

207
00:11:05,250 --> 00:11:08,650
Anyway, I'm going to bed. He who sleeps doesn't eat.

208
00:11:10,250 --> 00:11:11,850
Well, words of wisdom.

209
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:14,580
And you should go to bed too.

210
00:11:14,650 --> 00:11:15,950
But it's half past six.

211
00:11:16,450 --> 00:11:19,550
Well, high time. You shouldn't eat too much at night anyway.

212
00:11:20,250 --> 00:11:22,450
And I don't want to see this garbage here in the morning.

213
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:24,850
Give us five minutes.

214
00:11:57,510 --> 00:11:57,990
Good morning.

215
00:12:02,450 --> 00:12:03,550
No thank you, I won't be eating anymore.

216
00:12:04,550 --> 00:12:05,440
You're not going to eat?

217
00:12:05,650 --> 00:12:08,850
I'm surprised myself, but I feel quite full.

218
00:12:09,650 --> 00:12:10,950
And what do you know about this?

219
00:12:11,860 --> 00:12:12,740
And about this.

220
00:12:18,950 --> 00:12:20,250
Were you sleeping?

221
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:23,850
So I see someone really does eat in their sleep here.

222
00:12:28,450 --> 00:12:33,150
It's a few minutes past midnight and we're still waiting for the male of the species homo sapiens to appear.

223
00:12:35,750 --> 00:12:39,450
Lexa, can you take your hand off my leg?

224
00:12:41,550 --> 00:12:43,250
Sorry, I got confused.

225
00:12:43,750 --> 00:12:44,750
Yeah, with what exactly?

226
00:12:45,050 --> 00:12:45,850
Well, with mine.

227
00:12:47,950 --> 00:12:49,550
Look, it's not enough to just catch him in the act.

228
00:12:50,050 --> 00:12:51,250
I think he's sleepwalking.

229
00:12:51,250 --> 00:12:53,410
Starving during the day and raiding the fridge at night.

230
00:12:53,430 --> 00:12:55,070
Only hard evidence will convince him.

231
00:12:55,850 --> 00:12:57,450
Let's hope you can pull this off.

232
00:12:57,870 --> 00:12:58,350
Don't worry.

233
00:12:59,110 --> 00:13:01,550
Night photos are my specialty, I practice on the internet.

234
00:13:01,630 --> 00:13:02,870
Discreet yet sharp.

235
00:13:05,150 --> 00:13:09,050
Well, now I'm not only not scared anymore, I can't see anything either.

236
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:10,080
Let's go.

237
00:13:57,430 --> 00:13:58,370
Good morning!

238
00:14:00,850 --> 00:14:02,510
Man, finally they'll believe I'm sleepwalking.

239
00:14:02,850 --> 00:14:06,150
They wouldn't believe you even if you photographed a wedding thief.

240
00:14:06,370 --> 00:14:06,850
Jesus.

241
00:14:08,750 --> 00:14:13,150
Hey, why are you all up so early?

242
00:14:13,290 --> 00:14:15,970
I've still got the rest of the Maxi Giant in the fridge, so I got up early.

243
00:14:16,190 --> 00:14:18,450
Wrong, you don't, it duly departed in the night.

244
00:14:19,350 --> 00:14:20,870
It was still relatively fresh.

245
00:14:21,350 --> 00:14:22,250
Where'd it go?

246
00:14:22,850 --> 00:14:24,950
Come on, bro, why don't you try what I'm doing?

247
00:14:24,950 --> 00:14:27,570
A few days of abstinence and I don't even miss food.

248
00:14:27,690 --> 00:14:29,790
And there's a cozy little room in our tummy.

249
00:14:30,650 --> 00:14:33,490
No wonder, when there's a Maxi Giant sitting in there.

250
00:14:33,650 --> 00:14:34,650
What do you mean?

251
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:35,830
Like this.

252
00:14:39,050 --> 00:14:42,050
Well well, you ate it with chocolate.

253
00:14:42,550 --> 00:14:44,950
But that can't be me.

254
00:14:48,650 --> 00:14:52,650
Good lord, I have no idea what to do about this, but it would make a nice poster.

255
00:14:53,450 --> 00:14:55,330
No, I need to take measures.

256
00:14:55,330 --> 00:14:55,970
This can't go on.

257
00:14:56,650 --> 00:14:58,050
One for all, all for one.

258
00:14:59,490 --> 00:15:01,290
It's your duty to support me.

259
00:15:01,410 --> 00:15:03,630
Don't make that face, bro, it'll only do you good.

260
00:15:05,650 --> 00:15:06,950
What are we having for lunch?

261
00:15:18,050 --> 00:15:20,350
Well, see, I think it's getting better.

262
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:20,640
What?

263
00:15:21,050 --> 00:15:23,050
And it'll get even better?

264
00:15:23,450 --> 00:15:26,480
This morning it occurred to me that I should stop eating for good.

265
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:28,400
Not eating isn't the solution.

266
00:15:28,580 --> 00:15:29,880
You can eat as much as you want.

267
00:15:30,450 --> 00:15:34,650
Bro, I never thought I'd say this, but she's right.

268
00:15:35,350 --> 00:15:36,250
But only this.

269
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:37,380
I've been snacking on it for years.

270
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:38,660
And look at me.

271
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:40,060
It's an excellent thing.

272
00:15:42,250 --> 00:15:43,050
Try it.

273
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:48,650
I'm just terrified by the thought that it's made from the same material as the packaging.

274
00:15:48,650 --> 00:15:51,050
Puffed rice and corn husks.

275
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:54,160
Delicious.

276
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:56,740
So delicious I'll save it for later.

277
00:15:56,740 --> 00:15:57,020
Thank you.

278
00:15:58,250 --> 00:15:58,850
And you?

279
00:15:59,850 --> 00:16:04,030
Well, I'll just take an advance and pop out for goulash with six dumplings.

280
00:16:04,030 --> 00:16:05,270
Don't give him anything.

281
00:16:06,850 --> 00:16:08,950
The weight loss machine cost a fortune.

282
00:16:10,450 --> 00:16:11,550
Don't you have something to eat?

283
00:16:12,750 --> 00:16:14,550
Anything, pal, even just a roll.

284
00:16:18,450 --> 00:16:19,450
Damn.

285
00:16:27,950 --> 00:16:28,550
Please.

286
00:16:29,250 --> 00:16:31,150
For a schnitzel or a candy bar.

287
00:16:32,150 --> 00:16:33,150
You know, but...

288
00:16:34,150 --> 00:16:37,250
I get it, I know, but at least a piece of salami.

289
00:16:38,050 --> 00:16:40,170
Hey, what are you doing in there?

290
00:16:40,450 --> 00:16:42,150
Why is everyone running away?

291
00:16:42,250 --> 00:16:45,660
Are you forbidding them from buying popular music? Come here right now.

292
00:16:45,660 --> 00:16:46,640
You'll be at the register.

293
00:16:47,140 --> 00:16:58,870
What are you doing?

294
00:17:00,190 --> 00:17:00,630
Food.

295
00:17:02,050 --> 00:17:02,950
Are you hungry?

296
00:17:03,740 --> 00:17:04,180
Food.

297
00:17:10,650 --> 00:17:11,950
Think that'll be enough?

298
00:17:12,250 --> 00:17:14,050
I also put an alarm inside.

299
00:17:14,550 --> 00:17:15,810
Dad, I need to tell you something.

300
00:17:16,050 --> 00:17:16,550
Iva, show me your teeth.

301
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:18,350
You've been eating strudel.

302
00:17:18,350 --> 00:17:18,790
What?

303
00:17:18,990 --> 00:17:20,130
Of course, strudel.

304
00:17:20,170 --> 00:17:21,310
Do you know how many calories are in it?

305
00:17:21,510 --> 00:17:23,130
I've only had toothpaste since this morning.

306
00:17:23,270 --> 00:17:24,110
Toothpaste?

307
00:17:24,110 --> 00:17:26,050
Do you know how many calories are in toothpaste?

308
00:17:26,110 --> 00:17:26,550
Dad.

309
00:17:26,770 --> 00:17:26,990
Yeah.

310
00:17:27,550 --> 00:17:28,350
The pants.

311
00:17:29,150 --> 00:17:31,250
They actually must have shrunk after all.

312
00:17:31,850 --> 00:17:32,650
Are you mad?

313
00:17:34,350 --> 00:17:36,710
So I didn't gain weight?

314
00:17:37,350 --> 00:17:38,650
Well, apparently not.

315
00:17:40,650 --> 00:17:42,600
Ivuška, thank you.

316
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:43,340
And you know why?

317
00:17:44,050 --> 00:17:45,550
Because I feel wonderful.

318
00:17:46,650 --> 00:17:49,390
Did you know a person can survive without food for up to 60 days?

319
00:17:49,390 --> 00:17:50,730
And what will he do on day 61?

320
00:17:52,150 --> 00:17:53,450
We'll see, we'll see.

321
00:17:54,050 --> 00:17:56,050
Dad, if you slim down like this.

322
00:17:56,650 --> 00:17:59,910
I've never felt better in my life, and don't worry, I'll eat tonight.

323
00:17:59,910 --> 00:18:00,370
Look.

324
00:18:00,950 --> 00:18:01,630
I'll have this.

325
00:18:04,150 --> 00:18:34,950
So that's how it works.

326
00:18:40,550 --> 00:18:41,850
I see it did you good.

327
00:18:42,950 --> 00:18:44,150
I wouldn't touch this.

328
00:18:44,950 --> 00:18:46,650
It was the mice.

329
00:18:46,850 --> 00:18:47,850
Mice?

330
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:48,460
When?

331
00:18:48,620 --> 00:18:49,120
Where?

332
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:49,320
Where?

333
00:18:49,320 --> 00:18:49,740
How many?

334
00:18:49,780 --> 00:18:51,100
And how big are they?

335
00:18:51,180 --> 00:18:53,080
I don't know, they're definitely not small.

336
00:18:53,680 --> 00:18:56,200
Well, we definitely can't leave it like this.

337
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:57,440
I'll run and get mousetraps.

338
00:18:57,840 --> 00:18:58,340
Mousetraps?

339
00:18:58,440 --> 00:18:58,840
Yeah.

340
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:01,020
And you want to serve them this crap?

341
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:03,300
Look, they nibbled on it and left it alone.

342
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:04,080
I'll buy some cheese.

343
00:19:04,220 --> 00:19:04,680
Cheese.

344
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:09,420
Cheese, not a bad idea, but you know, these are city mice.

345
00:19:09,420 --> 00:19:11,340
Right, you can't impress them with just anything.

346
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:14,600
And I don't intend to impress them, I intend to kill them.

347
00:19:14,700 --> 00:19:16,080
Wait, every mouse has its own character.

348
00:19:16,650 --> 00:19:20,650
Some like Hungarian salami, some like ham, some like tripe soup.

349
00:19:22,950 --> 00:19:24,050
Tripe soup in a mousetrap?

350
00:19:25,550 --> 00:19:27,420
Well, it'll get messy all around.

351
00:19:27,550 --> 00:19:31,600
Yeah, alright, I guess you know better.

352
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:32,460
See you then.

353
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:33,000
Yeah, yeah.

354
00:19:33,450 --> 00:19:35,350
Oh, and olives, I forgot the olives.

355
00:19:38,150 --> 00:19:39,300
Those are the mice's favorite.

356
00:19:54,850 --> 00:19:55,980
Well, see that?

357
00:19:55,980 --> 00:19:56,320
What?

358
00:19:57,350 --> 00:19:59,110
Not even the traps are left.

359
00:19:59,110 --> 00:20:01,010
The critters dragged them off somewhere.

360
00:20:01,130 --> 00:20:03,010
But I don't see any droppings either.

361
00:20:03,690 --> 00:20:05,210
You can track mice?

362
00:20:05,290 --> 00:20:06,710
I mean mouse droppings and pellets.

363
00:20:06,890 --> 00:20:08,390
But we saw them.

364
00:20:08,470 --> 00:20:09,350
They were mice.

365
00:20:09,850 --> 00:20:10,570
This big.

366
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:12,150
Well then it's rattus norvegicus.

367
00:20:13,290 --> 00:20:14,710
And a big one at that.

368
00:20:14,810 --> 00:20:15,030
Yeah.

369
00:20:15,030 --> 00:20:19,810
But I didn't hire you for an expert consultation, I hired you for an expert extermination.

370
00:20:19,810 --> 00:20:20,450
Let's get to it then.

371
00:20:21,150 --> 00:20:27,430
We'll go with the classic mouse killer, it's cheap, it works fast, it's guaranteed.

372
00:20:27,430 --> 00:20:29,170
They croak in horrible convulsions.

373
00:20:29,250 --> 00:20:33,380
Marcelka, could I have a moment, about dad's diet.

374
00:20:33,580 --> 00:20:36,580
Ivuška, just a sec, I've got the pest control guy here.

375
00:20:36,760 --> 00:20:37,720
We have mice here?

376
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:39,020
What are you going to do with them?

377
00:20:39,020 --> 00:20:42,750
Nothing much, classic deratization, biological.

378
00:20:42,850 --> 00:20:45,960
Attractants without E-numbers, preservatives and such.

379
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:47,760
I thought you were going to poison them.

380
00:20:47,860 --> 00:20:48,660
Well, duh.

381
00:20:50,950 --> 00:20:53,950
How could I even think you'd help me with dad.

382
00:20:54,550 --> 00:20:57,050
If you're capable of killing someone just because they're hungry, then I'm at the wrong address.

383
00:20:58,430 --> 00:20:59,770
But Ivuška...

384
00:21:04,750 --> 00:21:05,580
Let her go.

385
00:21:05,850 --> 00:21:08,350
These eco-freaks, I run into them every day.

386
00:21:10,010 --> 00:21:11,190
They're all a bit nuts.

387
00:21:12,650 --> 00:21:13,550
Well, would you look at that.

388
00:21:14,450 --> 00:21:15,250
Here it is.

389
00:21:15,850 --> 00:21:16,920
But one more thing.

390
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:18,000
Well, what?

391
00:21:18,850 --> 00:21:20,250
This mouse killer extra.

392
00:21:20,950 --> 00:21:22,650
It's not exactly legal.

393
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:24,380
And it's more like banned.

394
00:21:24,380 --> 00:21:27,920
Some complications because of the Vietnam War or something, I don't know.

395
00:21:28,250 --> 00:21:32,020
Basically if anything happens, anything at all, call me first.

396
00:21:32,450 --> 00:21:34,650
Yes, the code word is Crisis, Crisis.

397
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:35,920
Crisis.

398
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:38,660
All the time, 24 hours a day I'm on the phone.

399
00:21:38,660 --> 00:21:39,020
Alright.

400
00:21:39,060 --> 00:21:39,500
Same here.

401
00:21:43,050 --> 00:21:43,850
Here you go, my mouse killer.

402
00:22:05,150 --> 00:22:06,500
Over my dead body.

403
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:07,120
Good night.

404
00:22:18,350 --> 00:22:21,250
The fridge is in the basement, it reminded dad of food.

405
00:22:22,050 --> 00:22:22,850
And where's the food?

406
00:22:23,450 --> 00:22:24,350
In the fridge.

407
00:22:25,950 --> 00:22:26,850
I'm going to the basement.

408
00:22:27,150 --> 00:22:29,550
But not ours, at Slavíková's.

409
00:22:32,610 --> 00:22:33,330
Have some.

410
00:22:40,350 --> 00:22:40,750
Ivuška, can I come in now, please, please.

411
00:22:42,620 --> 00:22:42,940
Hide it.

412
00:22:44,850 --> 00:22:46,880
See, nobody's eating here anymore.

413
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:48,270
Alright, I'm coming.

414
00:22:53,050 --> 00:22:55,450
See, you've already got a flat stomach.

415
00:23:10,050 --> 00:23:15,120
Iva, you've been eating here.

416
00:23:26,550 --> 00:23:30,050
It's dumplings, pork and cabbage.

417
00:23:31,420 --> 00:23:31,820
Smells good.

418
00:23:32,550 --> 00:23:34,250
It's pork.

419
00:23:37,950 --> 00:23:38,850
It's not.

420
00:23:39,450 --> 00:23:44,730
I was just tasting it.

421
00:23:44,730 --> 00:23:45,570
It's poisoned now!

422
00:23:46,050 --> 00:23:46,350
What?

423
00:23:49,850 --> 00:23:51,270
That's why it tasted so awful.

424
00:23:51,270 --> 00:23:52,790
And how much of it did you eat?

425
00:23:52,810 --> 00:23:54,150
This could kill you now.

426
00:23:54,530 --> 00:23:54,930
Kill?

427
00:23:55,010 --> 00:23:55,210
Yeah.

428
00:23:55,950 --> 00:23:59,350
I thought the worst it could cause is diarrhea.

429
00:23:59,950 --> 00:24:00,910
What have I done?

430
00:24:00,990 --> 00:24:01,630
What have I done?

431
00:24:01,630 --> 00:24:03,950
I knew I should have stuck with the Maxi Giant.

432
00:24:04,940 --> 00:24:05,400
Crisis!

433
00:24:05,540 --> 00:24:06,260
This is the end!

434
00:24:06,280 --> 00:24:06,920
This is the end!

435
00:24:06,960 --> 00:24:07,300
Crisis!

436
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:07,660
Crisis!

437
00:24:08,840 --> 00:24:11,040
So many things I didn't get to do in life.

438
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:13,300
Put together a zeppelin.

439
00:24:13,550 --> 00:24:15,250
Sing with Nirvana.

440
00:24:15,350 --> 00:24:15,750
Quick, come here.

441
00:24:16,860 --> 00:24:18,120
Ozzák's been poisoned.

442
00:24:20,020 --> 00:24:20,580
Ozzák!

443
00:24:21,690 --> 00:24:22,250
Ozzák!

444
00:24:22,910 --> 00:24:24,130
Ozzák, don't fall asleep.

445
00:24:24,410 --> 00:24:26,950
Try to throw it up.

446
00:24:26,950 --> 00:24:29,950
Bring me twelve beers and eight rums and I can try.

447
00:24:31,350 --> 00:24:32,250
What happened?

448
00:24:32,750 --> 00:24:34,750
Ozzák ate poisoned food.

449
00:24:35,050 --> 00:24:37,560
I always said his eating would kill him one day.

450
00:24:37,950 --> 00:24:39,050
I told you so, you.

451
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:39,760
You.

452
00:24:40,360 --> 00:24:42,180
It's all my fault.

453
00:24:42,380 --> 00:24:44,060
For God's sake, what happened?

454
00:24:44,950 --> 00:24:49,180
A child, a dog, or someone stupid enough to eat rat bait?

455
00:24:49,180 --> 00:24:52,640
How dare you talk about my brother like that, you scumbag?

456
00:24:52,820 --> 00:24:54,160
Dammit man, why did you eat it?

457
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:55,820
I was terribly hungry.

458
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:57,040
There's a picture on it.

459
00:24:57,500 --> 00:24:59,240
I thought it was the Megadeth logo.

460
00:24:59,480 --> 00:25:00,720
And can he still be saved?

461
00:25:01,580 --> 00:25:02,920
No need to call an ambulance.

462
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:04,440
We're equipped for cases like this.

463
00:25:04,500 --> 00:25:04,980
I'll be right there.

464
00:25:05,040 --> 00:25:05,980
I'll be right back.

465
00:25:05,980 --> 00:25:07,480
In case he goes into cardiac arrest or something.

466
00:25:07,540 --> 00:25:08,340
Do something.

467
00:25:11,550 --> 00:25:12,650
Don't worry, Marcelka.

468
00:25:13,150 --> 00:25:15,050
Don't blame yourself.

469
00:25:15,750 --> 00:25:16,550
I forgive you.

470
00:25:16,650 --> 00:25:17,250
Thank you.

471
00:25:17,830 --> 00:25:21,250
You have to promise me you'll listen to metal.

472
00:25:22,110 --> 00:25:22,710
I promise.

473
00:25:23,650 --> 00:25:25,450
Bro, swear it.

474
00:25:26,550 --> 00:25:30,250
Swear that from today you'll eat like a normal person.

475
00:25:30,450 --> 00:25:32,250
Eleven times a day.

476
00:25:35,550 --> 00:25:38,550
Call Aleš Brichta, I want to confess.

477
00:25:40,730 --> 00:25:41,490
Hold him!

478
00:25:42,050 --> 00:25:44,750
I want to die!

479
00:25:44,850 --> 00:25:45,960
I want to die!

480
00:25:46,150 --> 00:25:46,950
I want to die!

481
00:25:47,180 --> 00:25:47,660
Die!

482
00:25:48,250 --> 00:25:48,950
Die!

483
00:25:49,250 --> 00:25:50,050
Die!

484
00:25:52,450 --> 00:25:55,350
No hamster would survive being poisoned with that stuff.

485
00:25:55,650 --> 00:25:58,370
Jesus, from that can it was just cornflakes.

486
00:25:58,850 --> 00:25:59,710
Exactly.

487
00:26:01,050 --> 00:26:02,750
You know what, I actually feel good now.

488
00:26:03,150 --> 00:26:04,500
Kind of lighter, you know?

489
00:26:04,750 --> 00:26:08,600
Of course, they pumped half of the last Giant out of your stomach.

490
00:26:08,850 --> 00:26:10,950
And where did he put it?

491
00:26:12,040 --> 00:26:12,620
Uncle.

492
00:26:14,550 --> 00:26:18,760
Dad, how can you eat in front of a sick person when he can't?

493
00:26:19,050 --> 00:26:23,480
The diet is over. I promised Ozzák on his deathbed.

494
00:26:23,480 --> 00:26:25,460
Well, on his death counter.

495
00:26:28,750 --> 00:26:31,850
This view is worth laying down your life for.
